\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sarbian","CreatedById":57146,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-19T12:22:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell if you go the cmd line interface way then you have\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/154888-macckanapp/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lodger","CreatedById":126565,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-19T13:45:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIIRC \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E is a Mono Program. So if you have full Mono setup installed on your system (OS X / macOS, Linux, Windows) the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E client should work just fine.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fourfa","CreatedById":151713,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-20T04:35:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBe aware the Mono framework install is very heavy, and (if like many Macbook users) you\u0027re running on a smallish SSD drive, it can be a problem\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FL-T400","CreatedById":166421,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-22T01:48:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E will launch, it is just incredibly\u00A0glitchy and imputing text is weird\u00A0and laggy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"goldenpsp","CreatedById":113874,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-22T02:19:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222926934\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155161\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ip